Document: HingeJoint3D
Path: godot/classes/class_hingejoint3d.rst
Summary: Provides a 3D hinge joint that allows rotation around one axis.

HingeJoint3D

Inherits: Joint3D < Node3D < Spatial < Node < Object

A 3D hinge joint that allows rotation around one axis. This joint is useful for creating doors, levers, or any other object that pivots around a single point. It constrains the connected bodies' relative motion to a single degree of freedom, allowing them to rotate around the joint's axis.

Properties:
bias (float): The bias factor for the joint solver. This value controls how strongly the joint tries to maintain its constraints. A higher bias means a stronger constraint. Default: 0.3.
damping (float): The damping factor for the joint. This value controls how quickly the joint's motion is dampened. A higher damping means faster dampening. Default: 1.0.
enable_motor (bool): If true, the joint will attempt to reach a target angular velocity. Default: false.
gear (float): The gear ratio for the motor. This value determines the relationship between the target angular velocity and the actual angular velocity. Default: 1.0.
limit_above (float): The upper limit for the hinge's rotation in degrees. Default: 0.0.
limit_below (float): The lower limit for the hinge's rotation in degrees. Default: 0.0.
limit_softness (float): The softness of the rotation limits. A higher value makes the limits softer, allowing for some overshoot. Default: 0.0.
motor_max_force (float): The maximum force that the motor can apply to reach the target angular velocity. Default: 0.0.
param (float): The parameter for the joint. This value is used in conjunction with the joint's mode to control its behavior. Default: 0.0.
rotation (float): The current rotation of the hinge in degrees. Read-only.
spring (float): The spring constant for the joint. This value controls how strongly the joint tries to return to its rest position. Default: 0.0.
stop_erp (float): The error reduction parameter for the joint. This value controls how quickly the joint's constraints are enforced. Default: 0.8.
stop_mode (int): The stop mode for the joint. This determines how the joint behaves when it reaches its limits. Default: 0.
stop_threshold (float): The threshold for the joint's stop mode. This value determines when the stop mode is activated. Default: 0.0.
texture_filter (int): The texture filter mode for the joint. This property is not used by HingeJoint3D. Default: 0.
texture_repeat (int): The texture repeat mode for the joint. This property is not used by HingeJoint3D. Default: 0.
travel (float): The travel distance for the hinge. This value is used in conjunction with the hinge's limits to control its range of motion. Default: 0.0.
twist_limit_enabled (bool): If true, the hinge's rotation will be limited to the specified range. Default: false.

Methods:
set_param(param: int, value: float) → void
Sets a specific parameter of the joint. The available parameters are defined by the Joint3D.Param enum.

get_param(param: int) → float
Gets the value of a specific parameter of the joint. The available parameters are defined by the Joint3D.Param enum.
